full_text: With only three pass attempts, the Patriots recorded a -56.7% pass rate over expectation, the lowest-recorded PROE in the @nflfastR era (since 1999). The previous low was -44.9%, set last year in Week 12 by the Broncos when they didn't have any eligible QBs. #nflverse

@nflfastR has an xYAC model with which we can calculate Air EPA + xYAC EPA. I do that for completions and leave incompletions' EPA untouched. Interceptions are also untouched (no xYAC for the return). This is the result:
